# Supabase migrations

When you add or edit a file under `supabase/migrations/`:

1. Run `npm run db:migrate` to apply pending migrations to the linked Supabase database.
2. If the user already ran the same SQL manually in Supabase SQL Editor, run `npm run db:migrate -- --baseline` once so history is recorded without re-running SQL.
3. Use `npm run db:migrate -- --status` to see what is pending.

Requires `SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD` (or `SUPABASE_DB_URL`) in `.env.local` — see `.env.example`.

Do not ask the user to paste the database password in chat. If missing, tell them to add it to `.env.local` locally.
